Speaker A: Hello? Hello?
Speaker B: Yeah, so you were talking about Stapleton House, right?
Speaker A: Yeah, Stapleton House offered through ucl.
Speaker B: Okay.
Speaker A: House.
Speaker B: So since you want to know about Stapleton House firstly, I guess. Yeah, okay, so about Stapleton House, you can get up to three to four installments. Usually it's three installments for you to be like paying your rent. So for example, if you go for a classic ensuite, which is for 335 for the week, including all your municipal bills, then your total rent will be, or I say your total contract rent will be 70,085. So you can divide this 70,085 into three installments. So per installment it will come somewhere up to 5,695 pounds.
Speaker A: Okay, so and to reserve it, what do I have to pay? Because I'm waiting for like the accommodation offered by ucl, but I'll have a response from that like in mid September. So I need to know if I need to pay because I could be changing my accommodation last minute, basically. That's the catch.
Speaker B: Okay, you can, you can change your accommodation last minute. So what happens is you have also applied for the on campus accommodation, I believe. Could, could you.
Speaker A: I don't, I know, I, I don't quite hear you.
Speaker B: So did you also apply for the on campus accommodation or something like that?
Speaker A: Yeah, yeah, I did.
Speaker B: So you can, you also applied for the on campus accommodation directly to the UCO side. But. And did you check our website over the UCL website? Okay, got it, got it, got it. So you have applied for it and they said that it might take some time for, for you to get the response right.
Speaker A: I know, they told me. Yeah, they said like the first week of September.
Speaker B: But I like to have Stapleton House.
Speaker A: As a backup, you know, so. Yeah, if I don't get that, to.
Speaker B: Be very honest, Staples and House does require a deposit. Most of the properties, they do require deposit for you to book them. And for Staples and House it's somewhere around 250.
Speaker A: Around how much?
Speaker B: 200 to 250. It'll be somewhere around 200.
Speaker A: 250.
Speaker B: Let me check, let me confirm it for you. Just give me a moment. Yeah, 250. It's 250.
Speaker A: So 250 to reserve it.
Speaker B: Yeah.
Speaker A: And when, when after that do I pay like. So you should have to pay like in. I have to pay the monthly price, right?
Speaker B: Not each month. You will be provided specific date and your rent will be broken down into three to four installments.
Speaker A: Okay. Okay, got it.
Speaker B: Yeah. The first installment usually comes in August. But you can postpone it. Emailing the property with your scenario. You can just tell them that I am going through a little bit of issue. I want to postpone my first installment date to September. So then you'll have some time for you to pay the first rent installment. And till then you can also get the reply from your UCLS on site accommodation. Right, okay. But it's. It's 250.
Speaker A: 250 separate from that to just reserve it.
Speaker B: Yeah, not just. Not exactly reserving. And it's like an advanced rent. It'll be reducted from your.
Speaker A: Yeah, got it. Okay. Okay, great. Thank you. So, anything else I should know?
Speaker B: So do you. Would you like to proceed with the booking or anything? Not right now, but you might.
Speaker A: Now that I know everything. Yeah, I'll make a choice. I'll talk with my parents and stuff and I'll make a choice.
Speaker B: Got it. Got it. You can just drop a text whenever you decide to and you can even directly through our website, since I will be. How close.
Speaker A: How close is it to being full? Like, in how much of a rush am I to make a decision with.
Speaker B: Accommodation for Staples and House? Let me check the availability. How much rooms are available, since to be very honest, it's already September. As you can see, September is in the doorstep. So most of the properties are getting sold out. Stapleton House is on the. On the verge of getting sold out.
Speaker A: Okay. So I'll make a choice. Okay. Thank you.
Speaker B: Yeah. All right.
Speaker A: I'll text you when I have a decision. Thank you.
Speaker B: Thank you. Have a nice day. Bye.
Speaker A: Bye. You too.
